  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Figure 1 is an example of a Tool Definition plug-in. Note the definition of the Method Composer Tool standard category&#xD;
    in the Standard Categories section&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Figure 1: Tool Definition Plug-In Example&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;umf_tool_definition_base_plugin_example&quot; src=&quot;./resources/umf_tool_def_base_plugin_ex.gif&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Figure 2 is an example of how&amp;nbsp;practice-specific tool mentors are&amp;nbsp;assigned to a Tool standard category in a&#xD;
    Practice Base plug-in.&amp;nbsp;Specifically, how to assign the Method Composer tool mentors to the Method Composer Tool&#xD;
    standard category. The graphic on the left shows the definitions of the tool mentors (in the tool_guidance &amp;gt;&#xD;
    method_composer package) and the definition of the Tool standard category contributor (in the Standard Categories &amp;gt;&#xD;
    Tools) section. The graphic on the right shows how the tool mentors are assigned to the tool in the tool contributor&#xD;
    (the tool standard category &quot;owns&quot; these relationships).&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table title=&quot;Figure 2: Tool Mentor to Tool Assignment Example&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;2&quot; width=&quot;85%&quot;&#xD;
summary=&quot;tool_mentor_to_tool_assignment_example&quot; border=&quot;1&quot;>&#xD;
